nodes.text: A Consular-class cruiser was used by the Jedi Order in 32 BBY. The starship crashed into the swamps of Obredaan while two Jedi Masters were on an investigative mission.
A Consular-class cruiser was used by the Jedi Order. It was painted red in the livery of the Galactic Republic. Like other ships of its class, it was 115 meters and had three engine units.
The Consular cruiser was used by the Jedi Order in 32 BBY to transport two Jedi Masters, Plo Koon and Eeth Koth, to Obredaan to investigate the Jin'ha warriors.

During the mission, the starship crashed into the Obredaan swamps and rested in several pieces, while the two Jedi were captured. The wreckage was later discovered by Obi-Wan Kenobi and Qui-Gon Jinn, who were sent to finish the original mission.
The Consular-class cruiser appears in the second chapter of the 2001 video game Star Wars: Obi-Wan.
